Cape Town - A pedestrian was hit by a runaway boat trailer while walking along Tygervalley Road in Richwood, ER24 paramedics said. "A man, believed to be in his 20s, was injured when he was knocked over by a runaway boat on a trailer while walking along Tygervalley Road in Richwood in the Western Cape," ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said. "ER24 paramedics, along with Life Healthcare, arrived on the scene to find the man lying on the side of the road. A boat and trailer were found parked a short distance away. "Paramedics assessed the man an found that he had sustained an injury to his arm. "The man was treated for his injuries and was provided with pain-relief medication before he was transported to Karl Bremmer Hospital for further treatment. "It is understood that the trailer had come loose from a vehicle, causing it to veer off the road and crash into the pedestrian. "Authorities were on the scene to investigate further," Meiring said. Cape Argus